                                <i class="fa fa-plus-circle fa-3x"></i><strong> &nbsp; Input needed for the calculation of the grant element (entered in the Input-Output sheet): </strong>
                                <p class="text-muted">
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            Currency (repayment currency) of the loan, face value of the loan, upfront commission in percent, recurrent management fees, the interest rate charged on the loan, the maturity in years, the number of payments per annum, the grace period in years, and the principal repayment profile. The currency-specific CIRR discount rate is automatically obtained by selecting the currency in cell E13 in the Input–Output sheet. If a loan is contracted in a non-OECD currency (i.e., no CIRR is available), the SDR rate should be used. Please note that by choosing “other” as the currency, the calculator automatically selects the SDR rate.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            The grace period is defined as the period during which only the interest and no principal payments are payable by borrower to the creditor.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Based on the currency of the loan and maturity, the currency-specific CIRR interest rate is automatically taken from either six-month or ten-year averages from the sheet called <br>6-Month-10-Year CIRRs</br> and margins reflecting the maturity of the loan are automatically added to derive the discount rate. The spreadsheets will return the grant element in percent. Six-month averages are used for loans with a maturity of less than 15 years (column C). For all other loans the ten-year averages are used (column E). The following margins are added to the CIRRs: maturity "inferior" 15 years, 0.75 percent; maturity ≥15 years and "inferior" 20 years, 1.00 percent; maturity "superior or equal" 20 years and "inferior" ul 30 years, 1.15 percent; and maturity "superior or equal" 30 years, 1.25 percent. The discount rate used in the grant element calculation is the CIRR plus the relevant margin.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            All sheets calculate the grant element for financial packages that have a grant and a loan component.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Variable interest rates can be dealt with by manually entering applicable interest rates per payment period in “Column F,” of the relevant spread sheet based on the loan contract.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            Management fees not paid on a set schedule (i.e., per payment period or as a percentage of the outstanding loan amount) need to be entered manually (column H of the relevant worksheet).
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            For a custom principal repayment schedule, enter principal payments in column J of the relevant worksheet.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </p>
